# Trivy ignore file for LLMSafeSpaces.
#
# Format: each line is either:
#   - a CVE ID (e.g. CVE-2024-1234)
#   - a misconfig ID (e.g. KSV-0014)
#   - a CVE ID followed by `exp:YYYY-MM-DD` (expiration)
#
# Path-scoped ignores live in .trivyignore.yaml (separate file). This
# file is for IDs we accept globally with documented rationale.
#
# Reviewed quarterly: any expired ignores are re-triaged.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconfigurations: development manifests in local/ and security audit
# fixtures in design/stories/epic-17-security-review/phase-0*/ deliberately
# ship with weak security context to exercise specific scenarios. Production
# install path is the chart in charts/llmsafespaces/ which is hardened.
#
# We do NOT use a global ignore; instead .trivyignore.yaml scopes by path.
# Keep this file for global CVE accepts only.

# GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr — esbuild: missing binary integrity verification in Deno
# Not exploitable: esbuild is used as a Vite transpiler (server-side bundling),
# not as a Deno module resolver. The fix requires esbuild >= 0.28.1 which is
# incompatible with Vite 5 (drops destructuring transpile for ES2020 targets).
# Re-evaluate when upgrading to Vite 6+.
GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr exp:2026-09-13

# CVE-2026-53571 — vite: server.fs.deny bypass on Windows alternate paths
# Not exploitable: LLMSafeSpaces runs on Linux (Debian-based containers) only.
# The vulnerability affects Windows-specific alternate data stream paths which
# do not exist on Linux filesystems. Fix is available in vite 6.4.3/7.3.5/8.0.16;
# upgrade tracked separately from this bug fix.
CVE-2026-53571 exp:2026-09-15

# CVE-2026-13149 — brace-expansion: DoS via exponential-time complexity
# Transitive npm dev dependency (minimatch → brace-expansion) used by build
# tooling (eslint, vitest, etc.). Not shipped in any production image — the
# frontend Dockerfile runs `npm ci --omit=dev` and copies only the built
# dist/ into the nginx image. Re-evaluate when npm-lock.json is updated.
CVE-2026-13149 exp:2026-10-21

# CVE-2026-59869 — js-yaml: DoS via crafted YAML
# Transitive npm dev dependency used by build tooling (eslint, vitest,
# js-yaml CLI). Not shipped in any production image — the frontend
# Dockerfile runs npm ci --omit=dev and copies only the built dist/
# into nginx. Re-evaluate when npm-lock.json is updated.
CVE-2026-59869 exp:2026-10-21

# CVE-2026-13676 / CVE-2026-16221 — fast-uri: security policy bypass
# Transitive npm dev dependency (used by eslint/markdownlint). Not shipped
# in any production image — the frontend Dockerfile runs npm ci --omit=dev.
# Re-evaluate when npm-lock.json is updated.
CVE-2026-13676 exp:2026-10-21
CVE-2026-16221 exp:2026-10-21
